abstract: Authorities said Friday they have dealt an unprecedented blow to the violent MS-13 street gang, announcing charges against nearly 100 of the group's members and associates on Long Island.
snippet: Authorities said Friday they have dealt an unprecedented blow to the violent MS-13 street gang, announcing charges against nearly 100 of the group's members and associates on Long Island.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Authorities said Friday they have dealt an unprecedented blow to the violent MS-13 street gang, announcing charges against nearly 100 of the group's members and associates on Long Island.
headline_main: MS-13 Arrests Deal Blow to Gang Leadership on Long Island
headline_print_headline: MS-13 Arrests Deal Blow to Gang Leadership on Long Island

abstract: The U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention released a series of reports on Friday indicating that the outbreak of vaping-related lung injuries appears to be waning, as evidence mounts that vitamin E acetate, a cutting agent used in marijuana vape cartridges, is playing a role in the illnesses.
snippet: The U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention released a series of reports on Friday indicating that the outbreak of vaping-related lung injuries appears to be waning, as evidence mounts that vitamin E acetate, a cutting agent used in mariju...
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — The U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention released a series of reports on Friday indicating that the outbreak of vaping-related lung injuries appears to be waning, as evidence mounts that vitamin E acetate, a cutting agent used in marijuana vape cartridges, is playing a role in the illnesses.
headline_main: As U.S. Vaping Injuries Taper Off, New Evidence Points to Vitamin E
headline_print_headline: As U.S. Vaping Injuries Taper Off, New Evidence Points to Vitamin E

abstract: The U.S. Air Force said on Friday it has lifted a three-month ban on Boeing's KC-46A aerial refueling tanker for cargo and passenger operations after the aircraft maker fixed a problem related to locking down cargo.
snippet: The U.S. Air Force said on Friday it has lifted a three-month ban on Boeing's KC-46A aerial refueling tanker for cargo and passenger operations after the aircraft maker fixed a problem related to locking down cargo.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Air Force said on Friday it has lifted a three-month ban on Boeing's KC-46A aerial refueling tanker for cargo and passenger operations after the aircraft maker fixed a problem related to locking down cargo.
headline_main: U.S. Air Force Lifts Ban on Boeing KC-46A Tanker After Fix
headline_print_headline: U.S. Air Force Lifts Ban on Boeing KC-46A Tanker After Fix

abstract: A city employee in Winston-Salem, North Carolina, on Friday shot dead a fellow worker with whom he shared a "longstanding dislike," before the gunman was fatally shot by police, law enforcement officials said.
snippet: A city employee in Winston-Salem, North Carolina, on Friday shot dead a fellow worker with whom he shared a "longstanding dislike," before the gunman was fatally shot by police, law enforcement officials said.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - A city employee in Winston-Salem, North Carolina, on Friday shot dead a fellow worker with whom he shared a "longstanding dislike," before the gunman was fatally shot by police, law enforcement officials said.
headline_main: Police Call Fatal Shooting at North Carolina City Building 'Workplace Violence'
headline_print_headline: Police Call Fatal Shooting at North Carolina City Building 'Workplace Violence'

abstract: Washington state Republican lawmakers urged one of their own to resign after a state report found that he engaged in "domestic terrorism" against the United States by participating in armed conflict through the right-wing militia movement.

lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Washington state Republican lawmakers urged one of their own to resign after a state report found that he engaged in "domestic terrorism" against the United States by participating in armed conflict through the right-wing militia movement.
headline_main: Washington State Lawmaker Under Pressure to Step Down Over 'Domestic Terrorism'

abstract: Hear new seasonal tracks by Blink-182, Keith Urban, Macklemore and others.
snippet: Hear new seasonal tracks by Blink-182, Keith Urban, Macklemore and others.
lead_paragraph: Every Friday, pop critics for The New York Times weigh in on the week’s most notable new songs and videos. Just want the music? Listen to the Playlist on Spotify here (or find our profile: nytimes). Like what you hear? Let us know at theplaylist@nytimes.com and sign up for our Louder newsletter, a once-a-week blast of our pop music coverage.

abstract: The mayor of a Michigan steel town was attending his grandchildren's Christmas play Thursday evening when he got an unwelcome voicemail from an official of the town's top employer: United States Steel Corp.
snippet: The mayor of a Michigan steel town was attending his grandchildren's Christmas play Thursday evening when he got an unwelcome voicemail from an official of the town's top employer: United States Steel Corp.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — The mayor of a Michigan steel town was attending his grandchildren's Christmas play Thursday evening when he got an unwelcome voicemail from an official of the town's top employer: United States Steel Corp.
headline_main: U.S. Steel Delivers Unwelcome Christmas Surprise to Michigan Town
headline_print_headline: U.S. Steel Delivers Unwelcome Christmas Surprise to Michigan Town

abstract: The U.S. Justice Department and Federal Communications Commission filed in court on Friday to support a merger of T-Mobile and Sprint, the third- and fourth-largest wireless carriers.
snippet: The U.S. Justice Department and Federal Communications Commission filed in court on Friday to support a merger of T-Mobile and Sprint, the third- and fourth-largest wireless carriers.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Justice Department and Federal Communications Commission filed in court on Friday to support a merger of T-Mobile and Sprint, the third- and fourth-largest wireless carriers.
headline_main: U.S. Justice Department and FCC Fight State Effort to Block Merger of Sprint, T-Mobile
headline_print_headline: U.S. Justice Department and FCC Fight State Effort to Block Merger of Sprint, T-Mobile

abstract: Media company ViacomCBS Inc said on Friday it would take a 49% stake in film studio Miramax, owned by Qatar's BeIN Media Group, for $375 million.
snippet: Media company ViacomCBS Inc said on Friday it would take a 49% stake in film studio Miramax, owned by Qatar's BeIN Media Group, for $375 million.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Media company ViacomCBS Inc said on Friday it would take a 49% stake in film studio Miramax, owned by Qatar's BeIN Media Group, for $375 million.
headline_main: ViacomCBS to Take 49% Stake in Film Studio Miramax for $375 Million
headline_print_headline: ViacomCBS to Take 49% Stake in Film Studio Miramax for $375 Million

abstract: In the early 1970s, the dawn of what became known as hip-hop, he helped shape the art of graffiti on New York City subways. But he hated the word.
snippet: In the early 1970s, the dawn of what became known as hip-hop, he helped shape the art of graffiti on New York City subways. But he hated the word.
lead_paragraph: Phase 2, who in the early 1970s was one of the most prolific, inventive and emulated New York graffiti writers, and who later in his career produced early hip-hop’s most innovative fliers, died on Dec. 12 at a nursing and rehabilitation center in the Bronx. He was 64.
